{
  "stem": "27340.5",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were, of course, some real bastards amongst them, obviously.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There's no doubt about it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I think the majority of people, particularly today, while they still feel very, very affected by the sins of their fathers, for which one can hardly blame them, today's generation, at least, they are basically reasonable individuals.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You said that you felt England as your homeland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, that was quite an experience.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When I came back from Israel, I applied for British nationality, and having rejected it the first time when my parents were offered British nationality and granted it, because I found myself at variance with the then government's policy on Palestine.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were offered, and I was interviewed in 1947, I think.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Again, terrible upheaval between my father and myself, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He thought this was dreadful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But nevertheless, I made my own decision quite clearly, and I said, no, I'm at variance with the policy on Palestine, and in no way would I-- fair enough.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when I came back, I applied.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'd been out of the country, sum total, for just five years and one or two weeks, and therefore, I had to start serving all again.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I didn't apply again for British nationality until, I think, '58 or '59.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You had to chalk up another five years of residence.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, exactly that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I went for an interview.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I lived in London.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I went for an interview at the home office, and the normal sort of stoic and very stiff officialdom that exists between this exalted official and the nebbish of an individual who wants to become British.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this guy presented-- had a large book with him.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
